4. Edge Engine Specification
The edge engine is a multiplier-stack model. Each factor produces a multiplier (1.0x = no effect, 1.4x = strong effect). Multipliers are weighted and combined. The final edge percentage determines the chirp level.
Factor Weights
Factor
Weight
Data Source
What It Measures
Batter Power
0.35
MLB API (ISO, HR)
Current batter's isolated power vs pitcher handedness
Pitcher Fatigue
0.35
MLB API (pitch count, velo)
Pitch count, velocity drop from baseline, late innings
Wind
0.40
Open-Meteo + stadiums.json
Wind speed and direction relative to CF bearing
Park Factor
0.30
park_factors.json
Stadium run environment (100 = average)
Runner Situation
0.25
MLB API (runners, outs)
RE24 expected run matrix position
Temperature
0.20
Open-Meteo
Ball carry distance adjustment above/below 72°F


Edge Calculation
1. Each factor returns a raw multiplier (1.0x to ~1.5x)
2. Each multiplier is weighted by its factor weight
3. Weighted multipliers are summed
4. Soft cap applied at 10% (diminishing returns above)
5. Final edge % determines chirp level: 12%+ = Strong, 7-12% = Chirp, 4-7% = Soft
Edge Direction
The engine outputs a direction: OVER or UNDER. Wind out + high PF + power batter = OVER. Pitcher dominance + low PF + cold = UNDER. Direction is determined by the dominant factor cluster.

