6. Screen-by-Screen Spec
Navigation
Desktop: Fixed left sidebar (220px) with logo, nav items (Games, Chirps, History, Settings), live status indicator, chirp count badge.
Mobile (<768px): Sticky top header with logo + live badge. Fixed bottom tab bar with 4 tabs (Games, Chirps, History, Settings). Chirp count badge on Chirps tab.
Landing Page
  • Nav bar: logo + 'Get Started' CTA
  • Hero: headline 'See the edge before the line moves', subtext, email capture or CTA button
  • How It Works: 3 steps (scan, detect, alert)
  • Social proof / differentiators section
  • Footer with disclaimer: 'For entertainment purposes only'

Onboarding (3 steps)
  • Step 1: Pick your teams (grid of team logos, multi-select, 'Track All Teams' default)
  • Step 2: Alert preferences (toggle Strong/Regular/Soft chirps on/off)
  • Step 3: Confirmation ('You're all set' with summary)
  • Progress dots at top. Skip button. Green CTA at bottom.

Games Screen
  • Header: 'Games' title + 'Today · X games' subtitle
  • Game cards: away team vs home team, scores (if live), diamond (if live), venue, game status
  • Cards sorted: Live first, then scheduled, then final
  • Chirp badge on games that have active edges (+X.X%)
  • Tap card → Game Detail screen

Chirps Screen (Core Screen)
  • Header: 'Chirps' title + 'X active edges · Y live games'
  • Stat boxes (desktop only): Active Edges, Strong Chirps, Live Games, Avg Edge
  • Scoreboard strip: horizontal scroll of all games with chirp level indicator dots
  • Filter bar: All Chirps / Strong / Chirp / Soft
  • Chirp cards (responsive grid — 1 col mobile, 2 col tablet, 3 col desktop):
  •   — Level badge + edge % + timestamp
  •   — Scoreboard: logos, abbrs, names, scores, diamond, inning, outs
  •   — Batter/pitcher matchup cards (live games only, strong/chirp only)
  •   — Condition badges: wind, temp, PF, velo
  •   — Expandable 'WHY THIS CHIRP' factor breakdown with progress bars
  •   — O/U action bar at bottom: venue + suggested line
  • Scanning skeleton: shimmer loading state for games being analyzed
  • Empty state: cricket emoji + 'All quiet for now'
  • Tap O/U bar → Modal with full edge breakdown

Game Detail Screen
  • Back button → Games
  • Large scoreboard: team logos (48px), scores (40px mono), diamond, inning, outs
  • Edge card (if chirp exists): level badge, edge %, factor breakdown with progress bars, O/U recommendation
  • Game info card: venue, weather, park factor

History Screen
  • Header: 'History' title + 'Past chirp performance'
  • Stat row: Hit Rate %, Record (W-L), P&L ($)
  • Filter tabs: All / Hits / Misses
  • History cards: teams + line + edge % + actual result + P&L
  • Color-coded: green left border = hit, red = miss

Settings Screen
  • Account section: avatar, name, tier (Free Beta / Pro)
  • Chirp Alerts section: toggles for Strong/Regular/Soft
  • Notifications section: Push on/off, Sound on/off
  • Edge Engine section: read-only display of thresholds, data sources, version
  • Footer: version number, copyright


