11. MCP Tool Usage Guide
When to use each tool:
Tool
When to Use
When NOT to Use
GitHub MCP
Creating PRs, listing issues, reviewing code, managing branches. Use for ALL git operations instead of switching to browser.
Don't use for code writing itself — write code directly, use GitHub MCP to commit/push/PR.
21st.dev Magic
When you need a polished React component fast: cards, modals, navbars, toggles, form elements. Describe what you need naturally.
Don't use for custom data visualizations (Diamond, charts) or components tightly coupled to our data model.
Nano Banana
Hero images for landing page, social media assets, placeholder images, app store screenshots.
Don't use for UI components or icons — those should be SVG/code.
UI UX Pro Max
Background design intelligence when building any UI. Also use for design system searches: color palettes, font pairings, layout patterns.
Don't override our established design tokens with its suggestions — our tokens are already set.


Priority Order
1. GitHub MCP — use every day for commits, PRs, issues
2. 21st.dev Magic — use when building new UI components
3. UI UX Pro Max — let it run in background, consult for layout decisions
4. Nano Banana — use only when you need generated images

